4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING EDUCATION LAWS TO LIMIT THE STATE
5 PROMOTION OF TEACHER ATTENDANCE AT MEETINGS OF TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; PROHIBITING
6 PUPIL-INSTRUCTION-RELATED DAYS FROM BEING USED FOR ATTENDING STATE MEETINGS OF
7 TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; REMOVING THE MANDATE THAT TRUSTEES CLOSE SCHOOLS FOR THE
8 ANNUAL MEETINGS OF TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-1-304 AND 20-4-304,
9 MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 Section 1. Section 20-1-304, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "20-1-304. Pupil-instruction-related day. A pupil-instruction-related day is a day of teacher activities
15 devoted to improving the quality of instruction. The activities may include but are not limited to inservice
16 training, attending state meetings of teacher organizations, and conducting parent conferences. The activities
17 may not include attending state meetings of teacher organizations. A maximum of 7 pupil-instruction-related
18 days may be conducted during a school year, with a minimum of 3 of the days for instructional and professional
19 development meetings or other appropriate inservice training, if the days are planned in accordance with the
20 policy adopted by the board of public education. The days may not be included as a part of the required
21 minimum aggregate hours of pupil instruction."
22
23 Section 2. Section 20-4-304, MCA, is amended to read:
24 "20-4-304. Attendance at instructional and professional development meetings. The trustees of
25 a school district shall close the schools of the district for the annual instructional and professional development
26 meetings of teachers' organizations. A teacher may attend instructional and professional development meetings
27 without loss of salary or attend other appropriate inservice training that may be prescribed by the trustees
28 without loss of salary. If a teacher does not attend, the teacher may not be paid."
